I have been using a copy of Mike&#39;s Spiricomp design. I have 3, 12-469&#39;s scanning on FM, placed through a 4 channel mixer and then I run it through DC6 and Soundsoap2 with a 20 channel EQ. I use external stereo speakers that are spaced about 3 ft from me to allow the air to modulate the sounds better. It makes a difference, a big difference.

Regards,

Frank R.


----- Original Message ----
From: LC Duplatt &lt;lcdupla@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Friday, December 14, 2007 11:37:30 AM
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: The RS box out does itself again














            Frank R:



Yeah, the 12-469 has strong click noise on the AM scan, but much of 

it is not on the audio recording when I record it in a chamber, but I 

want to also be able to hear it in real time, so I am experimenting 

with different mics in the chamber and running into external 

speakers, etc.  Also, I want to slow the sound down a bit by building 

more of an echo chamber like Frank S has done (Bruce H. is slowing 

his recordings down 25%). I&#39;ll keep playing and reporting.



LC

http://www.AngelsGh osts.com



